n I use AI Scribe from the mobile app?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The Provider App includes the AI Scribe feature so you can dictate encounters or capture ambient conversations and have them converted into structured consultation notes, directly from your phone or tablet."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What types of consultations can providers manage in the app?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The app supports multiple consultation types:\n\nVideo visits for telehealth\n\nText consults for asynchronous communication\n\nIn-person visit support for documenting office encounters\n\nRemote monitoring for reviewing patient-generated health data and alerts"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How is the Provider App more secure than texting patients directly?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Unlike SMS, WhatsApp, or personal calls, the Provider App uses encrypted, HIPAA-appropriate messaging that keeps PHI safe, protects your personal phone number, and creates an auditable record of patient communications."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can providers get compensated for out-of-clinic communication using the app?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, where regulations and payer policies allow, the Provider App makes it easier to document, track, and bill for out-of-clinic communications such as asynchronous e-visits. The app time-stamps and records these interactions in the patient's health record."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does the app replace my desktop or web EHR?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. The Provider App is designed as a mobile companion to the Virtual Practice web platform. It brings key clinical features to your phone but does not replace the full web dashboard for administrative and configuration tasks."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is the Provider App free or do I need to pay extra?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Every Virtual Practice account includes the free Virtual Pract